## Adding New Tools

Create a new file in `tools/`:

```typescript
// tools/my-tool.ts
import { z } from 'zod';

export default {
  description: 'What your tool does',
  parameters: z.object({
    param1: z.string(),
    param2: z.number().optional()
  }),
  execute: async ({ param1, param2 }) => {
    // Your logic here
    return 'result';
  }
};
```

## Using with Claude Desktop

Add to your `claude_desktop_config.json`:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "{{PROJECT_NAME}}": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["simple-mcp", "serve", "/absolute/path/to/{{PROJECT_NAME}}/tools/example.ts"]
    }
  }
}
```

